column6: Tula Pink - Slow & Steady - Grandstand - Blue Raspberry
column8: There once was a speedy hare who bragged about how fast he could run. Tired of hearing him boast, Slow and Steady, the tortoise, challenged him to a race. All the animals in the forest gathered to watch. Hare ran down the road for a while and then paused to rest. He looked back at Slow and Steady and cried out, “How do you expect to win this race when you are walking along at your slow, slow pace?” Hare stretched himself out alongside the road and fell asleep, thinking, “There is plenty of time to relax.” Slow and Steady walked and walked. He never, ever stopped until he came to the finish line. The animals who were watching cheered so loudly for Tortoise, they woke up Hare. Hare stretched and yawned and began to run again, but it was too late. Tortoise was over the line. After that, Hare always reminded himself, “Don’t brag about your lightning pace, for Slow and Steady won the race!”

column7: 15 Original Quilt Projects from Kathy Doughty of Material Obsession.
column8: Your illustrated guide to developing an artful understanding of your quilting process. In its 15 original projects, you’ll be inspired to experiment with textiles, tools, and techniques to create vibrant quilts. As you add these new “layers” of complexity into your designs, you’ll discover added interest and depth in your quilting experience.

column7: Prints include a beautiful peony print on black a peony border stripe with lots of cutting options a tone-on-tone Sashiko texture cranes in flight two smaller florals and a cloudlike texture with lovely gold dots.
column8:
The Akahana collection features an Asian panel with two graceful red-crowned cranes in flight on a background of bright red peonies and swirling ribbons reminiscent of the traditional ribbon dance. The cranes, peonies, and ribbons are enhanced with fine gold metallic highlights that add an elegant touch. Companion prints include a beautiful peony print on black, a peony border stripe with lots of cutting options, a tone-on-tone Sashiko texture, cranes in flight, two smaller florals, and a cloudlike texture with lovely gold dots.

Simply frame the panel with the border stripe and layer, quilt, and bind for a quick wall hanging. The collection is also perfect for pieced quilts, table runners, placemats, and pillows featuring fan, kimono, tea bowl, and lantern blocks. Or, have a little fun with the panel and stitch up the stunning quilt and tablemat designed by Gina Gempesaw for the Akahana collection.

column8:
These great tools are used for glue stick appliqué, there are two tools in the pack. 
Used in conjunction with appliqué paper and a glue stick pen. The pronged tool is used in your left hand (if you're right handed) to steady the appliqué shape and the second tool which has a iron shaped end is used in your right hand to turn the edge of the fabric over to the wrong side and press in place.

A collaboration of friendship and design by Judie Rothermel and Vicki Bellino.

Originally released as a block of the month, this pattern contains all 6 pattern releases to enable completion of the quilt top. Papers for paper piecing are also included.

The original pattern as pictured was made using fabrics from the Aunt Grace collection by Judie Rothermel.

If you would like to have similar 1930's style fabrics selected for you and priced as a kit to make this pattern, just let me know by email or give me a call.

Finished quilt size is 82" x 82".

column7: Adorable Gifts Quilts and Wearables for Wee Ones by Kim Diehl & Pat Wys
column8:
Baby Bliss

Adorable Gifts, Quilts, and Wearables for Wee Ones

Kim Diehl & Pat Wys

Description

Grandmas, aunties and mums-to-be: if there's a baby on the way, you want fast, practical gifts, handmade with love. Be the hit of the baby shower with adorable projects designed by two popular authors and proud grandmothers. Cute, colourful and grandma approved!

  • Choose from a great selection of clothing, accessories, bibs, quilts, receiving blankets and more
  • Darling styles suited for boys and girls are sure to be loved by new mums
  • "Baby Talk" tip boxes offer hints for successful stitching with knit fabric, ultra-plush fabric, ribbon, rickrack and more

column7: A fabulous set for beginners; based on a 3 x 3 grid 6 pieces can make at least 9 different blocks.
column8: A fabulous set for beginners; based on a 3 x 3 grid, 6 pieces can make at least 9 different blocks.

column7: Based on a 4 x 4 grid these 7 pieces can made an amazing number of blocks.  Basic instructions are given for 7 blocks with diagrams for 3 more and suggestions for block changes to increase the number.  Play around and experiment!
column8: Based on a 4 x 4 grid, these 7 pieces can made an amazing number of blocks.  Basic instructions are given for 7 blocks, with diagrams for 3 more and suggestions for block changes to increase the number.  Play around and experiment!

column6: Bally Hall by Di Ford-Hall: Birds of a Feather - Dusty Rose
column8:
About Bally Hall The Irish connection to this fabric line begins with an early 19th century quilt from Ireland. Bally Hall is derived from the Gaelic phrase “baile na” which means “place of. ” I live in a beautiful rural area in Australia, so "place" is important to my inspiration. — Di Ford-Hall

Orders may be placed in whole metre units, or part thereof. i.e. for a metre and a half of fabric, please enter 1.5 in the quantity box. Minimum cut is 30 centimetres (i.e. 0.30 in the quantity box).

column8:
You can clearly see how the colors flow into each other and you absolutely see the lighter and darker spots on the quilt. What you don’t see on the picture are the numerous Hot Fix Swarovski ® crystals all over the quilt in the colors of the fabric.

Hang this quilt on your wall, with proper lighting, and every time thequilt will move by a gust of wind or you walking by and you see the sparkling colors all over the quilt.

There is a pattern available to make this quilt using the paper foundation method.

Finished size 65” x 74”

column7: Betsy's Basket by Darlene Zimmerman - 1930's Reproduction Toile
column8:
Betsy's Basket by Darlene Zimmerman is a 1930's reproduction collection.

Darlene is widely known for her 1930s reproduction fabrics, known as the “Granny” lines; these were collections designed over the past seven years with Chanteclaire fabrics. As a textile historian, Darlene has a large collection of vintage fabrics and quilts from which she frequently draws inspiration for her designs. Little Darlings, Clothesline Prints and Prima Cotton Solids were the first of Darlene’s collections to be producted in coordination with Robert Kaufman Fabrics.

column7: <div><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-family: comic sans ms cursive;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-style: italic;">Bloc Loc Ruler Set 1.5� to 6.5&rdquo
column8:
Bloc Loc is a revolutionary new channel technology to allow you to accurately “ square up ” a half square triangle block while eliminating slipping and ruler rock completely.

The Patent Pending Bloc Loc technology locks on to the seam allowance and allows the quilter to square up in just seconds.

There’s no need for a turntable. 
 
 
 
 
 
There is no need to lift the ruler.
 
Simply place the ruler onto the block, slide it so it locks onto the seam allowance, trim the first two sides. Then turn the block with Bloc Loc “locked on” and trim the other two sides.

It can be folded out to form a fabric covered ironing board. One of the inside covers is covered with sandpaper (this makes it easy to mark lines and patterns on fabric as it prevents it from slipping); the other inside cover has a cutting mat with grid marks (cm) and angle lines. Between the two covers there is an anti skid sheet - this holds the ironing board in place and protects the work surface.

column7: Fancy Forest is a delightful sampler quilt featuring some of her most popular block designs
column8:
ABOUT THE QUILT 
Fancy Forest is a delightful sampler quilt featuring some of her most popular block designs, including Fancy Fox, Hazel Hedgehog, Bunny, Allie Owl (in a new smaller size), Thistle, and newcomer Frances Firefly. The 67" x 91" Large Quilt is perfect for a single bed or to use as a sofa/large lap quilt. The 35" x 47" Small Quilt makes a perfect baby quilt or wall hanging. All blocks are sewn with simple straight and diagonal seams. No templates or paper piecing!

The "Memory Lane" series is inspired by the 1920's with its innovative fashion and colours The Charleston and Art Deco.
column8:
The "Memory Lane" series is inspired by the 1920's, with its innovative fashion and colours, The Charleston, and Art Deco.  

The patterns comprise both classic and more modern floral designs.  Colours such as bluish-black, olive green, and off-white with hints of turquoise result in a beautiful, interesting combination for a style that is both classic and perfect for today.  The series is excellent for both patchwork quilts and formal bags.

column7: Cabbage Rose is a playful series inspired by colourful characters like 1950s Lucille Ball and Astrid Lindgren's Pippy Longstocking.
column8:
Cabbage Rose is a playful series inspired by colourful characters like 1950s Lucille Ball and Astrid Lindgren's Pippy Longstocking.

Designs with rabbits and flowers in soft orange, blue/green, red, and pink give the series a sweet and colourful feel - perfect for pleasant patchworks quilts combined with folklore appliqués.  Cabbage Rose is an homage to "everyday roses" who inspire and add colour to life with their creativity and joie de vivre.

column7: Kindred Spirits 2 features magnificent prints inspired by Civil War era fabrics authentically reproduced in a variety of warm and cozy russets greens browns creams blues and reds.
column8: Kindred Spirits II is the highly anticipated sequel to Jill Shaulis of Yellow Creek Quilt Designs’ Kindred Spirits I. Kindred Spirits 2 features magnificent prints inspired by Civil War era fabrics, authentically reproduced in a variety of warm and cozy russets, greens, browns, creams, blues and reds. These prints will encourage you to appreciate the time honored tradition of hand crafting quilts for your home. Kindred Spirits II is ideal for scrappy quilts, home décor and wall hangings that will easily fit into a color wall for use season after season. It was designed in mind to coordinate beautifully with the Kindred Spirits I collection.

column8: Combine vibrant medallion prints with luscious textures in a rich palette of colors. You’ve described Paula’s new Kismet collection!  Paula is known for her symmetrical designs that can be cut apart and reassembled into fascinating designs. This latest collection has unique medallions (in two sizes!) as well as stripes and a spectacular allover. Each print is offered in a variety of colorways - all so tempting, you’ll find it hard to choose. The accompanying textures are sure to become part of your color wall!

column7: The "Memory Lane" series is inspired by the 1920's with its innovative fashion and colours The Charleston and Art Deco.
column8:
The "Memory Lane" series is inspired by the 1920's, with its innovative fashion and colours, The Charleston, and Art Deco.  

The patterns comprise both classic and more modern floral designs.  Colours such as bluish-black, olive green, and off-white with hints of turquoise result in a beautiful, interesting combination for a style that is both classic and perfect for today.  The series is excellent for both patchwork quilts and formal bags.

column7: Cabbage Rose is a playful series inspired by colourful characters like 1950s Lucille Ball and Astrid Lindgren's Pippy Longstocking.
column8:
Cabbage Rose is a playful series inspired by colourful characters like 1950s Lucille Ball and Astrid Lindgren's Pippy Longstocking.

Designs with rabbits and flowers in soft orange, blue/green, red, and pink give the series a sweet and colourful feel - perfect for pleasant patchworks quilts combined with folklore appliqués.  Cabbage Rose is an homage to "everyday roses" who inspire and add colour to life with their creativity and joie de vivre.

Designs with rabbits and flowers in soft orange, blue/green, red, and pink give the series a sweet and colourful feel - perfect for pleasant patchworks quilts combined with folklore appliqués.  Cabbage Rose is an homage to "everyday roses" who inspire and add colour to life with their creativity and joie de vivre.

column7: The "Memory Lane" series is inspired by the 1920's with its innovative fashion and colours The Charleston and Art Deco.
column8:
The "Memory Lane" series is inspired by the 1920's, with its innovative fashion and colours, The Charleston, and Art Deco.  

The patterns comprise both classic and more modern floral designs.  Colours such as bluish-black, olive green, and off-white with hints of turquoise result in a beautiful, interesting combination for a style that is both classic and perfect for today.  The series is excellent for both patchwork quilts and formal bags.

column8:
Penny's Pets by Darlene Zimmerman
Darlene is widely known for her 1930s reproduction fabrics, known as the “Granny” lines; these were collections designed over the past seven years with Chanteclaire fabrics. As a textile historian, Darlene has a large collection of vintage fabrics and quilts from which she frequently draws inspiration for her designs. Little Darlings, Clothesline Prints and Prima Cotton Solids were the first of Darlene’s collections to be producted in coordination with Robert Kaufman Fabrics.

Cabbage Rose is a playful series inspired by colourful characters like 1950s Lucille Ball and Astrid Lindgren's Pippy Longstocking.
column8:
Cabbage Rose is a playful series inspired by colourful characters like 1950s Lucille Ball and Astrid Lindgren's Pippy Longstocking.

Designs with rabbits and flowers in soft orange, blue/green, red, and pink give the series a sweet and colourful feel - perfect for pleasant patchworks quilts combined with folklore appliqués.  Cabbage Rose is an homage to "everyday roses" who inspire and add colour to life with their creativity and joie de vivre.

column7: The "Memory Lane" series is inspired by the 1920's with its innovative fashion and colours The Charleston and Art Deco.
column8:
The "Memory Lane" series is inspired by the 1920's, with its innovative fashion and colours, The Charleston, and Art Deco.  

The patterns comprise both classic and more modern floral designs.  Colours such as bluish-black, olive green, and off-white with hints of turquoise result in a beautiful, interesting combination for a style that is both classic and perfect for today.  The series is excellent for both patchwork quilts and formal bags.

column8:
FRENCH COUNTRY, C. 1850 by Sara Morgan
The French Country look continues to be widely popular because it can be used in traditional designs or transformed into a contemporary style. Rich and delicate motifs, resist-dyed flowers, paisleys, and floral sprigs are captured in beautiful detail. The handwriting reproductions are perfectly orchestrated and these classic colorings never go out of style.

column6: Snow Leopard Designs - Natural World - Butterfly Wings~Tropical
column8:
“Natural World” by Snow Leopard Designs. The "Natural World" collection from Snow Leopard Designs reflects the beauty that we find everywhere in the visible universe. In the great oceans we see the vivid patterns of tropical fish and the colours of seashells and coral. In the sky we find the multi-coloured feathers of birds and the textures and shapes of eggs. On the land we find all the varied forms of animal and plant life. All of the designs have been carefully hand-painted and many developed from antique lithographic prints in the Snow Leopard Designs archive. Selected fabrics available. 
 
Orders may be placed in whole metre units, or part thereof. i.e. for a metre and a half of fabric, please enter 1.5 in the quantity box. Minimum cut is 30 centimetres (i.e. 0.3 in the quantity box).

column6: Stonington by Denyse Schmidt  - Snowflake Medallion
column8:
Stonington Collection by Denyse Schmidt
Stonington, a new fabric collection from Denyse Schmidt, perfectly captures the strength, independence, and beauty of Denyse’s New England Yankee sensibility, with an endearingly familiar touch of 1970s inspired fashion and decor. Like the trends of that era, Stonington straddles a folk/preppy/western vibe with cool understatement. Think 70s rock stars, vintage jumpers and shirts, patchwork everything, tiered skirts with ruffles, lots of prints mixed together, big floppy hats, wide legged pants, and bandanas.

Orders may be placed in whole metre units, or part thereof. i.e. for a metre and a half of fabric, please enter 1.5 in the quantity box. Minimum cut is 30 centimetres (i.e. 0.3 in the quantity box).

Gerri Robinson creates country cottage florals in her Summer Cottage collection by Red Rooster Fabrics.

Premium 44 inch wide cotton fabric.

Gerri says, "Summer Cottage was inspired by all things summer: bright, clean, clear colors of sunshine yellows, sky blues, grass greens, strawberry reds, blueberry blues, and pristine white." You'll find all of these colors in her appealing ribbon floral with sprays of flowers, pretty bows, and flowery streamers. A blue and yellow allover floral, three small florals, and a crisp texture complete this cheerful collection.

Gerri says, "Summer Cottage was inspired by all things summer: bright, clean, clear colors of sunshine yellows, sky blues, grass greens, strawberry reds, blueberry blues, and pristine white." You'll find all of these colors in her appealing ribbon floral with sprays of flowers, pretty bows, and flowery streamers. A blue and yellow allover floral, three small florals, and a crisp texture complete this cheerful collection.

column8: Quiltworx.com Leaf Series is a new series of small projects designed by Quiltworx.com inspired by, Leaves.  With contemporary layouts either taking the shape of leaves or with pieced backgrounds, these patterns are designed to make the leaf the focus of every project.  This pattern features Judy’s newest foundation paper piecing technique, Curved Paper Piecing.  And, once the leaf is complete, it is bound and appliqued to the background to give a contemporary, bold impression, perfect as a form of wall art and decorative feature to any decor.

column7: The "Memory Lane" series is inspired by the 1920's with its innovative fashion and colours The Charleston and Art Deco.
column8:
The "Memory Lane" series is inspired by the 1920's, with its innovative fashion and colours, The Charleston, and Art Deco.  

The patterns comprise both classic and more modern floral designs.  Colours such as bluish-black, olive green, and off-white with hints of turquoise result in a beautiful, interesting combination for a style that is both classic and perfect for today.  The series is excellent for both patchwork quilts and formal bags.

column7: Cabbage Rose is a playful series inspired by colourful characters like 1950s Lucille Ball and Astrid Lindgren's Pippy Longstocking.
column8:
Cabbage Rose is a playful series inspired by colourful characters like 1950s Lucille Ball and Astrid Lindgren's Pippy Longstocking.

Designs with rabbits and flowers in soft orange, blue/green, red, and pink give the series a sweet and colourful feel - perfect for pleasant patchworks quilts combined with folklore appliqués.  Cabbage Rose is an homage to "everyday roses" who inspire and add colour to life with their creativity and joie de vivre.

column6: The Meanderings of a Quilt Collector
column7: Jane Lury is a passionate quilt collector. Her meanderings in all the continents to bring back exceptional quilts enabled her to collect Persian embroideries boutis and more. This book is illustrated with more than 200 wonderful photos
column8: Jane Lury is a passionate quilt collector. Her meanderings in all the continents to bring back exceptional quilts enabled her to collect Persian embroideries, boutis and more. This book is illustrated with more than 200 wonderful photos and traces a story with historical comments of her textile researches. An outstanding book!

column7: Treasures from the Barn by Linda Collins

column8:
Tree of Life Palampore Panel size is 47" x 87".

The name Palampore means a large bedspread or coverlet.  This is a
reproduction of a typical Palampore hand painted in England ca. 1775. 
The "tree of life" motif is typical of most palampores and is a symbol
to celebrate birth, marriage and special occasions!

column6: Tula Pink - Slow & Steady - Clear Skies - Blue Raspberry
column8: There once was a speedy hare who bragged about how fast he could run. Tired of hearing him boast, Slow and Steady, the tortoise, challenged him to a race. All the animals in the forest gathered to watch. Hare ran down the road for a while and then paused to rest. He looked back at Slow and Steady and cried out, “How do you expect to win this race when you are walking along at your slow, slow pace?” Hare stretched himself out alongside the road and fell asleep, thinking, “There is plenty of time to relax.” Slow and Steady walked and walked. He never, ever stopped until he came to the finish line. The animals who were watching cheered so loudly for Tortoise, they woke up Hare. Hare stretched and yawned and began to run again, but it was too late. Tortoise was over the line. After that, Hare always reminded himself, “Don’t brag about your lightning pace, for Slow and Steady won the race!”

Victoria Findlay Wolfe - Meadow Storm - Chevron Black
column8: Victoria Findlay Wolfe's new collection for Studio 37 was "inspired by living on the farm and harvesting the food we grew. Minnesota weather is always interesting!" Designs such as Cloudy, Misty, Overcast, and Sunshowers suggest the amazing displays in a prairie sky. Victoria combines timeless elements with a graphic approach to create a fresh and modern Meadow Storm, including a black-white version of the Manor Stripe from Mostly Manor.

Designs such as Cloudy, Misty, Overcast, and Sunshowers suggest the amazing displays in a prairie sky. Victoria combines timeless elements with a graphic approach to create a fresh and modern Meadow Storm, including a black-white version of the Manor Stripe from Mostly Manor.

column8:
Vliesofix is a wonderful product for Applique.

 It's very light weight which means you do need to stitch it down after ironing. Other wise during wash it could start lifting.

But the benefit for lightweight is that generally when you are appliqueing you have layers and they will still feel pretty pliable and easy to sew.

Where as when you use a heavier weighted product though you don't need to stitch it, it will be quite stiff and not very gentle on the machine needle.

 

30cm x 30cm

Price given is per metre
